'''Sport''' noun.
* That which diverts, and makes mirth; pastime; amusement.
* Mock; mockery; contemptuous mirth; derision.
* Plural athletic endeavor
* A toy; a plaything; an object of mockery.
* Play of some kind, e.g. word play
* Gaming for money as in racing, hunting, fishing
* (Botany, Zoology, Biology) A plant or an animal, or part of a plant or animal, which has some peculiarity not usually seen in the species; an abnormal variety or growth. 
* (slang) A sportsman; a gambler.